text.tspan: Internationally observed elections by Western monitors
Estimates correspond to the number of international elections that were either observed and criticized by Western
monitors, observed and not criticized by Western monitors, or elections that were not observed by Western
monitors. Criticism refers to allegations of significant vote-fraud.
Note: Includes 2435 election events in 162 countries
